                <title>Townships</title>
                <geoform>vector digital data</geoform>
            </citeinfo>
        </citation>
        <descript>
            <abstract>Townships are identified with both a township and range designation.  Townships are generally numbered from a north/sout baseline, designated as either north or south.  Ranges are generally numbered from an east/west baseline, designated as either east or west.   Townships are typically divided further into 1 mile sections.</abstract>
            <purpose>Townships are typically a 6 mile square grid that is a subdivision of the public land survey system (PLSS).</purpose>
        </descript>
